narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Only if Francesco is Teaching, or your very good at italian. Passed L1 and L2, but L3 is VERY HARD unless you have a great grasp on the language.
Only if you need it for the language requirement
A review of L1/L2. If you'd like to finish your language requirement or continue with Italian, it's obviously a requirement, but know that it's a bit boring. Definitely do-able as a fifth credit.
RE-cap of all the concepts from L1-L2 but more in depth
It's the same as 110 or 120 just new material (even though a lot is a repeat from 120).
It's a fun way to finish off your language requirement. There are quite a few tests though, which can be annoying.
I would recommend it highly, Italian is a beautiful language.

I would say that it is a great introductory language course that follows a very logical progression at a suitable pace. I would definitely recommend it to anyone wishing to improve their Italian skills.
